Last month, I had the privilege of being invited as the first alumni from the Computer Science & Business Systems department of Rajalakshmi Institute of Technology, to deliver a guest lecture on placement preparation.

With around 1.5 years of internship experience and 9 months of work experience, I wasn’t completely sure if I was eligible to give an alumni talk. But I chose to take it as an opportunity to share my placement journey, the companies I went through, and how things eventually worked out for me.

I began the session on a positive note and spoke about the importance of building a strong resume, gaining the right internship experience, understanding different interview rounds, preparing for GDs, and performing well in technical interviews. I also shared a compilation of resources that personally helped me during my placement journey.

I would like to sincerely thank the Head of the Department, Dean, and faculty members of CSBS department for this wonderful opportunity. It was truly a meaningful experience for me.

I didn’t take up this session because I knew everything. When I was at their stage, I didn’t really have someone to guide me on what to prepare or how to approach placements. I had to figure things out on my own. So I took this as a golden opportunity to share a few words from my experience, hoping that something I shared, would help them gain some clarity and move closer to their dream jobs!

